# Contributing

Thanks for wanting to help out with this project! We're keeping things pretty simple, but we do have a basic workflow to keep the code from turning into a mess. 

## Getting in Touch

If you want to contribute, aren't sure where to start, or if you get stuck trying to figure out how to make a branch or a PR, reach out. I'm happy to help you get it sorted.

* GitHub: [@npcoiner](https://github.com/npcoiner)
* Email: [nicholascoiner@gmail.com](mailto:nicholascoiner@gmail.com)

## Branching & Pull Requests

We do all our work in branches and merge them using Pull Requests (PRs). Please try to refrain from pushing code straight to the main branch.

When you create a new branch, use one of these prefixes so it's easy to tell what you're working on:

* `feat/short-description` - for new features
* `fix/short-description` - for fixing bugs
* `refactor/short-description` - for cleaning up or restructuring code
* `docs/short-description` - for updating documentation
* `test/short-description` - for adding or fixing tests
* `chore/short-description` - for minor maintenance tasks

## Submitting Your Work

Once your branch is good to go, open a Pull Request. Just drop a quick note in the description about what you changed and why. Someone will review it (maybe yourself), and then we'll get it merged.
